description: Lists the namespaces for the specified Amazon Web Services account. This operation doesn't list deleted namespaces.

parameters.name: AwsAccountId
parameters.description: The ID for the Amazon Web Services account that contains the Amazon QuickSight namespaces that you want to list.

nested_items.name: Namespaces
nested_items.description: The information about the namespaces in this Amazon Web Services account. The response includes the namespace ARN, name, Amazon Web Services Region, notification email address, creation status, and identity store.

nested_items.name: CapacityRegion
nested_items.description: The namespace Amazon Web Services Region.

nested_items.name: CreationStatus
nested_items.description: The creation status of a namespace that is not yet completely created.

nested_items.name: IdentityStore
nested_items.description: The identity store used for the namespace.

nested_items.name: NamespaceError
nested_items.description: An error that occurred when the namespace was created.

nested_items.name: IamIdentityCenterApplicationArn
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) for the IAM Identity Center application.

nested_items.name: IamIdentityCenterInstanceArn
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) for the IAM Identity Center instance.

nested_items.name: NextToken
nested_items.description: A unique pagination token that can be used in a subsequent request. Receiving NextToken in your response inticates that there is more data that can be returned. To receive the data, make another ListNamespaces API call with the returned token to retrieve the next page of data. Each token is valid for 24 hours. If you try to make a ListNamespaces API call with an expired token, you will receive a HTTP 400 InvalidNextTokenException error.

nested_items.name: RequestId
nested_items.description: The Amazon Web Services request ID for this operation.

nested_items.name: Status
nested_items.description: The HTTP status of the request.
